We love our politics drunk and disorderly.The fact that we cheer on our favourite politicians for saying things for which our grandmothers would kill us reinforces the commonly held belief that we are a nation of hypocrites. This week, the National Cohesion and Integration Commission (NCIC) went with a thermo gun to Msambweni to take political temperatures, and it gagged at the first speech they scanned.
They returned with a verdict that neither of the two top contenders could lay claim to a clean campaign, concluding that whoever would come up with a detergent that would clean up the political filth Kenyans witnessed around the campaign venues would be a contender for the next Nobel Prize in Chemistry.



