Impeachment
Look at the impeachment of Governor Mike Sonko and the content that was being aired on the Senate floor as evidence of his bad manners. Words that my editor cannot allow to pass on this paper for public consumption were coming out freely from the former governor’s tongue.
You would have thought his mouth would cost him votes, but Mike Sonko received close to a million votes in the last election, despite Nairobi voters being exposed to his unrefined character that even a professional street brawler would be embarrassed to take on.
We might pretend that we love clean and mature politics but deep down we know that given a chance we would drink from a sewage tanker and throw toys off the pram.
The fact that we cheer on our favourite politicians for saying things for which our grandmothers would kill us reinforces the commonly held belief that we are a nation of hypocrites.
We pretend to love politicians of high integrity but we keep voting for ruffians who trade in vile manners and chew public money like ball gum.





This country needs divine intervention to save it from itself, and the first step is for everyone to get the new improved mouthwash that kills 99 per cent of dental germs responsible for verbal diarrhoea.



